The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 2010 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. The proclamation highlights the significance of music in African-American culture and its role in uniting individuals through a shared heritage. It acknowledges the contributions of African-American singers, composers, and musicians to the nation and the world. The article also emphasizes the historical importance of African-American music in conveying the struggles and achievements of the community. It mentions various musical genres such as gospel, jazz, blues, rock and roll, and hip-hop, which have shaped America's cultural landscape. The proclamation calls for the celebration and promotion of African-American music through various activities and programs.